{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7b87e3df",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# M3 paper example"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "e9bdac0a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from qiskit import *\n",
    "from qiskit_ibm_runtime.fake_provider import FakeGuadalupe\n",
    "import mthree\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "plt.style.use('quantum-light')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f95aaa4c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Setup experiment"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "8a1882a3",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "backend = FakeGuadalupe()\n",
    "qubits= [1,4,7,10,12,13,14,11,8,5,3,2]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "aaf9674a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1381.08x806.68 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 3,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "N = 12\n",
    "qc = QuantumCircuit(N)\n",
    "\n",
    "qc.x(range(0, N))\n",
    "qc.h(range(0, N))\n",
    "\n",
    "for kk in range(N//2,0,-1):\n",
    "    qc.ch(kk, kk-1)\n",
    "for kk in range(N//2, N-1):\n",
    "    qc.ch(kk, kk+1)\n",
    "qc.measure_all()\n",
    "qc.draw('mpl')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "3b2fb3ef",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Calibrate M3 mitigator, execute circuits, and compute raw and corrected expectation values"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "50bf92cc",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "mit = mthree.M3Mitigation(backend)\n",
    "mit.cals_from_system(qubits)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "fc1541f0",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "trans_circs = transpile([qc]*10, backend, initial_layout=qubits)\n",
    "raw_counts = backend.run(trans_circs).result().get_counts()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "5bd4306e",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "raw_exp = []\n",
    "for cnts in raw_counts:\n",
    "    raw_exp.append(mthree.utils.expval(cnts))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "08a506e8",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "quasis = mit.apply_correction(raw_counts, qubits, return_mitigation_overhead=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "10f24a71",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Plot results\n",
    "\n",
    "Here we plot the two distributions of expectation values.  Mitigated is closer to the exact result, $\\sim 0.446$, given by the dashed vertical line."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "b3a46780",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "(0.0, 0.5)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 8,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 360x504 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig = plt.figure(figsize=(5,7))\n",
    "gs = fig.add_gridspec(2, hspace=0.1)\n",
    "axs = gs.subplots(sharex=True, sharey=True)\n",
    "axs[0].hist(raw_exp, bins=5, color='#009d9a')\n",
    "axs[0].legend(['Raw counts'], fontsize=12)\n",
    "axs[0].axvline(0.446, color='k', linestyle='--')\n",
    "\n",
    "axs[1].hist(quasis.expval(), bins=10, color='#a56eff')\n",
    "axs[1].legend(['M3 tensored mitigation'], fontsize=12)\n",
    "axs[1].axvline(0.446, color='k', linestyle='--')\n",
    "\n",
    "axs[1].set_xlabel('Expectation value', fontsize=14)\n",
    "for ax in axs:\n",
    "    ax.label_outer()\n",
    "    ax.tick_params(labelsize=12)\n",
    "plt.xlim([0,0.5])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "2030dcc9",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Look at mitigation overhead\n",
    "\n",
    "The distribution in the above plot is wider for the mitigated expectation values than for the raw results.  This is due to the mitigation overhead that we can extract from the quasi-probabilities"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "id": "8d442d0d",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "4.431798846398797"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 10,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "np.mean(quasis.mitigation_overhead)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0e2eac24",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "that together with the shots gives us the standard deviation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "id": "589d7bcc",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "0.06567026467943002"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 11,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "np.mean(quasis.stddev())"
   ]
  },
  {

   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "e76aa223",
